Subject:    <a href="?t=95837891200020&r=1&w=2">Why use WKS records?</a>
From:       <a href="?a=95837786400022&r=1&w=2">blake!oregon!dsmith () beaver ! cs ! washington ! edu  (Dale Smith)</a>
Date:       <a href="?l=namedroppers&r=1&w=2&b=198908">1989-08-18 14:52:54</a></font>
[Download RAW <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626985&q=mbox">message</a> or <a href="?l=namedroppers&m=95837784626985&q=raw">body</a>]</b>

In the interest of keeping the number of RRs down (and my zone files
smaller/faster to xfer, etc), I have decided that the WKS records that I
used to keep were useless.  Nobody uses them (at least nothing I've
found that I care about), and they are a pain to keep reasonably
up-to-date (so they never are anyway).  The upshot of this is that I no
longer carry WKS records for any hosts in the zones I manage.  Anybody
have any comments? Am I making a terrible blunder?

Any thoughts on this subject would be appreciated.

